			<div id = "comment-9343" class = "comment">
				<p>You can use the PI (or an arduino, which is easier) as a dumb hardware interface.
Plugin the device at your laptop's usb port and then send from the computer commands, the hardware interface gets the command and then write or read a port.
I did something with an arduino due. I designed a Hardware board and now I have a fully functional industrial PLC, which has some modularity.
I can send commands from the PC and my controller just switches or read the inputs.</p>
